In v4 you called the `Machine({...})` factory directly; in v5 you call `setup({ types }).createMachine({...})` (or plain `createMachine` when you don't need typed events). The body is nearly identical — states, `initial`, `on` — but `setup` is where types, actions, and guards live so the machine body stays narrow and inferable.

```ts
